Note: Helper Functions
Process called "create_empty_byte_array" that takes size as Integer returns ByteArray:
    Note: Create an empty byte array of specified size
    Let data be list containing
    For i from 0 to size minus 1:
        Add 0 to data
    Return ByteArray with:
        data as data
        size as size

Process called "string_to_byte_array" that takes string as String returns ByteArray:
    Note: Convert string to byte array
    Let data be list containing
    For each char in string:
        Add char.to_byte to data
    Return ByteArray with:
        data as data
        size as length of data

Process called "url_decode" that takes value as String returns String:
    Note: Decode URL-encoded string
    Let decoded be value
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "+" and new as " "
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%20" and new as " "
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%21" and new as "!"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%22" and new as "\""
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%23" and new as "#"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%24" and new as "$"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%25" and new as "%"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%26" and new as "&"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%27" and new as "'"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%28" and new as "("
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%29" and new as ")"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%2A" and new as "*"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%2B" and new as "+"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%2C" and new as ","
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%2F" and new as "/"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%3A" and new as ":"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%3B" and new as ";"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%3D" and new as "="
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%3F" and new as "?"
    Set decoded to replace_all with string as decoded and old as "%40" and new as "@"
    Return decoded

Process called "split_string" that takes string as String and delimiter as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split string by delimiter
    Let parts be list containing
    Let current be ""
    For each char in string:
        If char is equal to delimiter:
            If current is not empty:
                Add current to parts
            Set current to ""
        Otherwise:
            Set current to current Joined with char
    If current is not empty:
        Add current to parts
    Return parts

Process called "trim_string" that takes string as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace
    Let start be 0
    Let end be length of string minus 1
    
    Note: Find first non-whitespace character
    While start is less than length of string:
        Let char be string[start]
        If char is not equal to " " and char is not equal to "\t" and char is not equal to "\n" and char is not equal to "\r":
            Break
        Set start to start plus 1
    
    Note: Find last non-whitespace character
    While end is greater than or equal to start:
        Let char be string[end]
        If char is not equal to " " and char is not equal to "\t" and char is not equal to "\n" and char is not equal to "\r":
            Break
        Set end to end minus 1
    
    If start is greater than end:
        Return ""
    Return substring with string as string and start as start and end as end plus 1

Process called "replace_all" that takes string as String and old as String and new as String returns String:
    Note: Replace all occurrences of old with new
    Let result be string
    While result contains old:
        Let index be result.index_of with substring as old
        If index is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let before be substring with string as result and start as 0 and end as index
            Let after be substring with string as result and start as index plus length of old
            Set result to before Joined with new Joined with after
        Otherwise:
            Break
    Return result

